cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Information-Theoretic Unification of General Relativity and Quantum Mechanics: Numerical Demonstration in 16 Phases"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We propose an Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) of general relativity
  and quantum mechanics in which spacetime, gravity, the Standard Model gauge
  group, matter generations, the electroweak Higgs mechanism, the cosmological
  constant, and chirality all emerge from a single axiom — the entanglement
  first law dS(rho_A) = d Tr[K_A^(0) rho_A]. We demonstrate this through 16
  independent numerical experiments on free-fermion lattice models and small
  quantum codes, verifying each emergent phenomenon to precisions ranging
  from machine precision (Standard Model gauge group, Atiyah-Singer index,
  Higgs gap, cosmological constant scaling) through 0.04% (Page curve, AdS_5
  geodesic distance) to order-of-magnitude (Yukawa hierarchies). The same
  axiom is shown to operate in 1D, 2D, and 3D boundary CFTs, reproducing
  AdS_3, AdS_4, and AdS_5 / CFT_4 (real-world 4D quantum gravity) bulks.
  Six concrete experimental verification proposals are provided, four of
  which have already been partially realised in cold-atom and superconducting
  quantum simulator experiments. The framework provides a minimal,
  verifiable skeleton for unifying GR with QM through quantum information.
keywords:
  - quantum gravity
  - holography
